וָה);","strongs_def":"a ship (as a fixture)","kjv_def":"ship.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"ship(4x)"},"H6717":{"id":"H6717","lemma":"צִיבָא","translit":"Tsîybâʼ","pron":"tsee-baw'","derivation":"from the same as H6678 (צוֹבָא); station;","strongs_def":"Tsiba, an Israelite","kjv_def":"Ziba."},"H6718":{"id":"H6718","lemma":"צַיִד","translit":"tsayid","pron":"tsah'-yid","derivation":"from a form of H6679 (צוּד) and meaning the same;","strongs_def":"the chase; also game (thus taken); (generally) lunch (especially for a journey)","kjv_def":"[idiom] catcheth, food, [idiom] hunter, (that which he took in) hunting, venison, victuals.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"venison(8x), hunter(3x), victuals(2x), provision(2x), hunting(1x), catch(1x), food(1x)"},"H6719":{"id":"H6719","lemma":"צַיָּד","translit":"tsayâd","pron":"tsah'-yawd","derivation":"from the same as H6718 (צַיִד);","strongs_def":"a huntsman","kjv_def":"hunter.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"hunter(1x)"},"H6720":{"id":"H6720","lemma":"צֵידָה","translit":"tsêydâh","pron":"tsay-daw'","derivation":"or צֵדָה; feminine of H6718 (צַיִד);","strongs_def":"food","kjv_def":"meat, provision, venison, victuals.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"victuals(6x), provision(2x), meat(1x)"},"H6721":{"id":"H6721","lemma":"צִידוֹן","translit":"Tsîydôwn","pron":"tsee-done'","derivation":"or צִידֹן; from H6679 (צוּד) in the sense of catching fish; fishery;","strongs_def":"Tsidon, the name of a son of Canaan, and of a place in Palestine","kjv_def":"Sidon, Zidon.","pos":"proper locative noun","usage":"Zidon(20x), Sidon(2x)"},"H6722":{"id":"H6722","lemma":"צִידֹנִי","translit":"Tsîydônîy","pron":"tsee-do-nee'","derivation":"patrial from H6721 (צִידוֹן);","strongs_def":"a Tsidonian or inhabitant of Tsidon","kjv_def":"Sidonian, of Sidon, Zidonian.","pos":"adjective patrial","usage":"Zidonians(10x), Sidonians(5x)"},"H6723":{"id":"H6723","lemma":"צִיָּה","translit":"tsîyâh","pron":"tsee-yaw'","derivation":"from an unused root meaning to parch;","strongs_def":"aridity; concretely, a desert","kjv_def":"barren, drought, dry (land, place), solitary place, wilderness.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"dry(7x), wilderness(2x), drought(2x), barren(1x)"},"H6724":{"id":"H6724","lemma":"צִיוֹן","translit":"tsîyôwn","pron":"tsee-yone'","derivation":"from the same as H6723 (צִיָּה);","strongs_def":"a desert","kjv_def":"dry place.","pos":"masculine noun"},"H6725":{"id":"H6725","lemma":"צִיּוּן","translit":"tsîyûwn","pron":"tsee-yoon'","derivation":"from the same as H6723 (צִיָּה) in the sense of conspicuousness (compare H5329 (נָצַח));","strongs_def":"a monumental or guiding pillar","kjv_def":"sign, title, waymark.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"title(1x), waymark(1x), sign(1x)"},"H6726":{"id":"H6726","lemma":"צִיּוֹן","translit":"Tsîyôwn","pron":"tsee-yone'","derivation":"the same (regularly) as H6725 (צִיּוּן)lemma צִיוּן missing dagesh, corrected to צִיּוּן;","strongs_def":"Tsijon (as a permanent capital), a mountain of Jerusalem","kjv_def":"Zion.","pos":"proper locative noun","usage":"Zion(153x), Sion(1x)"},"H6727":{"id":"H6727","lemma":"צִיחָא","translit":"Tsîychâʼ","pron":"tsee-khaw'","derivation":"or צִחָא; as if feminine of H6704 (צִחֶה); drought;","strongs_def":"Tsicha, the name of two Nethinim","kjv_def":"Ziha.","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Ziha(3x)"},"H6728":{"id":"H6728","lemma":"צִיִּי","translit":"tsîyîy","pron":"tsee-ee'","derivation":"from the same as H6723 (צִיָּה);","strongs_def":"a desert-dweller, i.e. nomad or wild beast","kjv_def":"wild beast of the desert, that dwell in (inhabiting) the wilderness.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"desert(3x), wilderness(3x)"},"H6729":{"id":"H6729","lemma":"צִינֹק","translit":"tsîynôq","pron":"tsee-noke'","derivation":"from an unused root meaning to confine;","strongs_def":"the pillory","kjv_def":"stocks."},"H6730":{"id":"H6730","lemma":"צִיעֹר","translit":"Tsîyʻôr","pron":"tsee-ore'","derivation":"from H6819 (צָעַר); small;","strongs_def":"Tsior, 