.","pos":"proper locative noun","usage":"Zemaraim(2x)"},"H6788":{"id":"H6788","lemma":"צַמֶּרֶת","translit":"tsammereth","pron":"tsam-meh'-reth","derivation":"from the same as H6785 (צֶמֶר);","strongs_def":"fleeciness, i.e. foliage","kjv_def":"highest branch, top.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"top(3x)"},"H6789":{"id":"H6789","lemma":"צָמַת","translit":"tsâmath","pron":"tsaw-math'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"to extirpate (literally or figuratively)","kjv_def":"consume, cut off, destroy, vanish.","pos":"verb","usage":"destroy(5x), vanish(1x), consume(1x)"},"H6790":{"id":"H6790","lemma":"צִן","translit":"Tsin","pron":"tseen","derivation":"from an unused root meaning to prick; a crag;","strongs_def":"Tsin, a part of the Desert","kjv_def":"Zin.","pos":"proper locative noun","usage":"Zin(10x)"},"H6791":{"id":"H6791","lemma":"צֵן","translit":"tsên","pron":"tsane","derivation":"from an unused root meaning to be prickly;","strongs_def":"a thorn; hence, a cactus-hedge","kjv_def":"thorn.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"thorn(2x)"},"H6792":{"id":"H6792","lemma":"צֹנֵא","translit":"tsônêʼ","pron":"tso-nay'","derivation":"or צֹנֶה; for H6629 (צֹאן);","strongs_def":"a flock","kjv_def":"sheep.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"sheep(2x)"},"H6793":{"id":"H6793","lemma":"צִנָּה","translit":"tsinnâh","pron":"tsin-naw'","derivation":"feminine of H6791 (צֵן);","strongs_def":"a hook (as pointed); also a (large) shield (as if guarding by prickliness); also cold (as piercing)","kjv_def":"buckler, cold, hook, shield, target.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"shield(10x), buckler(5x), target(5x), hook(1x), cold(1x)"},"H6794":{"id":"H6794","lemma":"צִנּוּר","translit":"tsinnûwr","pron":"tsin-noor'","derivation":"from an unused root perhaps meaning to be hollow;","strongs_def":"a culvert","kjv_def":"gutter, water-spout.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"gutter(1x), waterspout(1x)"},"H6795":{"id":"H6795","lemma":"צָנַח","translit":"tsânach","pron":"tsaw-nakh'","derivation":"